Fix HQ load/clicks; quiet Helmet console warnings; stable auth token across deploys

Author HQ (pre-existing, surfaced post-split):
- /api/activity returns { entries }, not { events }; loadHQ read .events so
  `events` was the wrapper object and events.slice() threw → "Could not load
  HQ data". Now reads entries (tolerates array/legacy).
- Queried /api/projects (404s) not /api/projects/list, and ?limit not ?count —
  HQ stats were always empty. Fixed.
- Inline onclick referenced module-scoped fns (no-ops) → addEventListener.

Console noise (Helmet, gateway/src/index.ts): disable crossOriginOpenerPolicy
+ originAgentCluster — plain HTTP on the LAN, so the browser ignores COOP and
Origin-Agent-Cluster only logs a warning; neither adds value here.

Stable auth token across deploys (the actual cause of the /api/status 401
storm): each fresh container auto-generated a new BOOKCLAW_AUTH_TOKEN, so every
redeploy invalidated open dashboard tabs. Now mirror the vault key —
- docker-compose.yml passes BOOKCLAW_AUTH_TOKEN;
- deploy.sh resolves it (env → repo .env → generate + persist to repo .env) and
  writes it to docker/.env;
- openrouter-pipeline.sh reads the token via `docker exec printenv` first
  (env-provided), then the /app/.env fallback.

Verified: tsc clean; npm test green (34 unit + API + smoke). Helmet + HQ already
confirmed live on Mercury (COOP/OAC headers gone, HQ loads).
